      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /health - Service health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "x-request-id",
                "value": "postman-health-check",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:3000/health",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "3000",
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Checks the service dependencies: Postgres, SQS phase1, and SQS phase2. Returns 200 when all dependencies are ok and 503 when any dependency is down.\n\nCurl command:\n```bash\ncurl -s http://localhost:3000/health | jq\n```\n\nExample output:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"service\": \"ai-ticket-pipeline\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"database\": { \"status\": \"ok\", \"latency_ms\": 3 },\n    \"sqs_phase1\": { \"status\": \"ok\", \"latency_ms\": 12 },\n    \"sqs_phase2\": { \"status\": \"ok\", \"latency_ms\": 11 }\n  },\n  \"checked_at\": \"2026-04-29T00:00:00.000Z\"\n}\n```"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('health returns 200 or 503', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect([200, 503]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('response has status and dependencies', function () {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status');",
                  "  pm.expect(json).to.have.property('dependencies');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
