    {
      "name": "Tickets",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /tickets - Create ticket success",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "x-request-id",
                "value": "postman-create-ticket",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"subject\": \"Login broken\",\n  \"body\": \"I cannot log in to my account since yesterday.\",\n  \"submitter\": \"alice@example.com\",\n  \"tenant_id\": \"demo\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:3000/tickets",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "3000",
              "path": [
                "tickets"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Creates a ticket, saves it in Postgres with status queued, enqueues it to the Step 1 queue, and immediately returns 202. If successful, the test script stores response.ticketId into the ticketId collection variable.\n\nCurl command:\n```bash\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/tickets \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"subject\":\"Login broken\",\"body\":\"I cannot log in to my account since yesterday.\",\"submitter\":\"alice@example.com\",\"tenant_id\":\"demo\"}' \\\n  | jq\n```\n\nExample output:\n```json\n{\n  \"ticketId\": \"c1d6d148-4183-432a-8b6a-07233af725a5\",\n  \"status\": \"queued\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-29T00:00:00.000Z\"\n}\n```"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('create returns 202', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(202);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('response includes ticketId and queued status', function () {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.ticketId).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('queued');",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('ticketId', json.ticketId);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Created example",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
